The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Dec. 15: State-owned IDBI Bank today announced lowering interest rates to 8.25 per cent for home loans irrespective of the amount till March 2012. The offer is applicable to new customers applying on or before March 31, 2010, and taking a part or full disbursement during the period. After the offer period, interest rates will be charged based on the then prevailing floating rates, IDBI Bank said                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 15: Moodys has upgraded its outlook on the rupee-denominated bonds issued by the Indian government from stable to positive on the back of the strong economic recovery restoring confidence of investors in these instruments.                             
	 Mumbai, Dec. 15: A section of Air India employees owing allegiance to Air Corporation Employees Union has threatened to go on a strike from December 22 to protest the managements proposed move to withdraw some facilities from January 1.                            
	 New York, Dec. 15: Hospira a leading generic injectable pharmaceuticals company in the US  will acquire the Indian firm Orchid Chemicals generic injectable business for $400 million to get a direct presence in India.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 15: The Centre has asked South Koreas Posco to apply afresh for permission to set up a 12 million tonnes per annum steel plant in Orissa that has been held up for four years over land acquisition.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 15: State-run oil companies today cut jet fuel prices for the second time this month to ease the burden on cash-strapped airlines. The ATF price in Calcutta has been cut by Rs 663 per kilo litre to Rs 47,558.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 15: Tata Steels European arm Corus will invest 35 million euros (around Rs 238 crore) in its rail production facility in France as it has secured a contract worth 350 million euros from French railway operator SNCF.                                                                                                                          
